The paper deals with the problem of counting matchings and independent sets in graphs, which is a topic in discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The connective constant, which is a measure of the average degree of a graph, is a central concept in the paper and is extensively studied in graph theory (cs.CC). The paper also uses techniques from statistical physics and probability theory, which are relevant to the sub-categories of cs.GT (graph theory) and cs.SI (social and information networks).
